{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5de30e67-3f67-4b90-ac9f-bbc5f246ad2b","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key flag mappings:**\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (after `--`) |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nNote the `--` separator — on .NET 8 SDK, arguments after `--` are forwarded to the MTP test host. If you upgrade to .NET 9+ SDK, `dotnet test` gains native MTP support and the `--` separator is no longer needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0cca9bbe-2c87-4f38-89df-234bdab24e24","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences between VSTest and MTP:\n- `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` \n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (or using Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nWith MTP on .NET 8, you'd typically run the test executable directly rather than through `dotnet test`, since full MTP integration in `dotnet test` came later. Let me clarify what's actually available for the user's setup.\n\nThe flag mappings for MTP are: `--filter` stays the same, but `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx` (requiring the TrxReport package), and code coverage shifts to `--coverage` with the CodeCoverage package. The `--blame` functionality maps to `--hangdump` and related diagnostics flags.\n\nWhen running with `dotnet test`, you pass MTP arguments after `--`, or you can run the test project directly with `dotnet run` and pass the same flags.","outputTokens":1150,"requestId":"1BC9:361109:2207D69:256794C:6A03CEAC"},"id":"aaab1567-7657-4f34-88d0-dd82072eb7f3","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:07:11.861Z","parentId":"93585c39-c7c9-43ba-ae76-f1f4315b51be"}
